{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Hu et al.",
    "in 2014 studied two models for text matching [17], Architecture I (ARC-I) and ARC-II.",
    "The ARC-I model uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) to separately obtain features from texts and calculate the similarities between the features.However, there is no interaction between the texts while the features are extracted.• Interaction-focused Architecture: This architecture evaluates the relationship between a query and a document according to their interaction.",
    "Compared with representation-focused architecture, interaction-focused architecture can capture more contextualized information.",
    "proposed the ARC -II model [17], which uses a 1D convolutional layer to explore the interaction between input texts."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "in 2014 studied two models for text matching [17], Architecture I (ARC-I) and ARC-II.",
    "proposed the ARC -II model [17], which uses a 1D convolutional layer to explore the interaction between input texts."
  ]
